name: Hummus humor (Jeu de loi et Béatitudes)
description:
"Humility (n.) :
early 14c., "quality of being humble," from Old French umelite "humility, modesty, sweetness" (Modern French humilité), from Latin humilitatem (nominative humilitas), in Church Latin "meekness," from humilis "lowly, humble," literally "on the ground," from humus "earth," from PIE root *dhghem- earth."

A tribute to the Mother, from the ground of her power. With sense of humor, gravity falls in love.

Blessings children.
